    "created_at": "2015-06-14T10:50:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-14T10:50:18Z",
    "body": "Any ideas on how does this affect the performance ? Doesnt setting `LOAD_IGNORE_LIMITS` make request to be synchronous, wouldnt that be a negative effect ? As far as the http spec it doesnt seem to have upper thresholds on concurrent connections [now](https://httpwg.github.io/specs/rfc7230.html#persistent.concurrency). Any reason for this feature when SPDY or HTTP2.0 is there ?\n"
